# Safety Principles

- **ESP32 is never safety-critical** — Wi-Fi/Web/OTA failure must not stop vehicle operation.
- **Tablet is never required** — start, pumps, cooling, mandatory lighting work without UI.
- **STM32** owns real-time, VCM, power channels, kill enable chain.
- **No generic “all outputs OFF”** — safe state per function and failure mode (ECU power, fuel pump, fans, etc.).
- **Kill / battery isolation** — not solely firmware, ESP32, CAN, or Web UI; follow motorsport regulations.
- Config cannot override hardware current/PWM/retry limits.

Full rules: `drivecore-engineering.mdc` §6, `docs/001_System_Architecture.md`.
